Covid-19 confirmed cases rises to 24 264 with 43 new deaths reported Dr Zweli Mkhize, the Health Minister announced that the total number of confirmed Covid-19 cases in South Africa is 24 264. There is an increase of 649 positive cases Provincial Breakdown: Testing data 
A total of  605 991 tests have been conducted with 9 214  tests done in the last 24 hours. Deaths and Recoveries The total national deaths are: 524 New deaths: 43 (9-E/cape, 1-Gauteng, 33-W/Cape) Total Recoveries: 12 74, 53% recovery rate Gender Distribution Deaths : Gender Male %                           Female %                       Total 281(53.6%)                     243 (46.4%)                    524  